cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CR 

The paper uses computational social science methods to analyze online communities and their evolution, making it likely to fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The analysis also involves natural language processing to identify hateful speech, which could place it under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper focuses on misogynistic movements, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
